data.enText: to end; to make sth end

data.chText: 你的聘约十二月份到期。
data.enText: Your contract of employment terminates in December.

data.chText: 那项协议立即被终止了。

data.enText: to terminate a pregnancy (= to perform or have an abortion )

data.chText: 这趟列车的终点站是伦敦维多利亚火车站。
data.enText: This train terminates at London Victoria.

simple_means.memory_skill: termin 界限 + ate 使… → 到界限 → 结束

ex.chText: 做完家庭作业后，他就睡觉了。
ex.enText: After finishing his homework, he went to bed.

ex.chText: 你读完那本小说后给我看看。
ex.enText: Let me have the novel when you finish reading it.

ex.chText: 你通常什么时候吃完晚饭？
ex.enText: When do you finish your supper?

synonyms.bx: 最普通用词，指完成某事，常后接名词或动名词，但不可后接动词不定式；也指事件、活动或时期等结束。

ex.chText: 他完成了在欧洲的学业。
ex.enText: He accomplished his education in Europe.

ex.chText: 她因健康状况不佳而未能完成任务。
ex.enText: She failed to accomplish the task because she was in poor health.

synonyms.bx: 较正式用词，尤指通过努力成功地完成某事。

ex.chText: 大会主席向所有与会者表示感谢，就此结束了这次会议。
ex.enText: The chairperson closed the conference by extending his thanks to all the participants.
The party was closed with a sound of applause.

ex.chText: 影片以在伦敦重逢的激动场面结束。
ex.enText: The movie closed with an emotional reunion in London.

synonyms.bx: 尤指（使）某事物以某种方式结束。

ex.enText: Installation of the pipelines was completed last week.

ex.chText: 国民经济计划成功地完成了。
ex.enText: The national economic plan was successfully completed.

ex.chText: 他花了4年时间完成了在欧洲的学业。
ex.enText: It took him four years to complete his education in Europe.

synonyms.bx: 尤指经历较长时间后完成或做成某事物，通常用被动语态。

ex.chText: 这两个国家之间的战争于1898年结束。
ex.enText: The war between these two countries ended in 1898.

ex.chText: 那家工厂的工会同意两天之后结束罢工。
ex.enText: The labour union of the factory agreed to end the strike two days later.

ex.chText: 由于天气不好，聚会早早结束了。
ex.enText: The party ended early due to the bad weather.

synonyms.bx: 指局势、过程、活动等自然结束或被人为终止。

ex.chText: 他的聘约什么时候到期？
ex.enText: When will his contract of employment terminate?
The woman decided to terminate the pregnancy.

synonyms.bx: 指合同、协议等终止或使之终止；也作医学术语，指终止妊娠。

tr: bring to an end or halt
example: She ended their friendship when she found out that he had once been convicted of a crime
The attack on Poland terminated the relatively peaceful period after WW I

tr: discharge from an office or position
example: The boss fired his secretary today
The company terminated 25% of its workers

tr: have an end, in a temporal, spatial, or quantitative sense
example: the bronchioles terminate in a capillary bed
Your rights stop where you infringe upon the rights of other
My property ends by the bushes
The symphony ends in a pianissimo

tr: be the last or concluding part of
example: This sad scene ended the movie

value.def: When you terminate something or when it terminates, it ends completely.

example.ex: Her next remark abruptly terminated the conversation...
example.tran: 她接下来说的话使谈话戛然而止。

example.ex: His contract terminates at the end of the season.
example.tran: 他的合同在本赛季末终止。

example.ex: ...a dispute which led to the abrupt termination of trade.
example.tran: 导致贸易突然终止的一场争端

value.def: To terminate a pregnancy means to end it.

example.ex: After a lot of agonizing she decided to terminate the pregnancy...
example.tran: 经历一番痛苦挣扎后，她决定终止妊娠。

example.ex: In the world as a whole, about ten per cent of all pregnancies are terminated.
example.tran: 从全世界看来，所有怀孕的人中约 10% 的妊娠被终止了。

example.ex: You should also have a medical check-up after the termination of a pregnancy.
example.tran: 终止妊娠后还应该体检一次。

value.def: When a train or bus terminates somewhere, it ends its journey there.

example.ex: This train will terminate at Taunton.
example.tran: 这列火车的终点站是汤顿。

partsOfSpeech.dec: de 加强 + termin 界限 + e → 加强界限 → 限定
de 加强 + termin 界限 + ed，determine 的形容词 → 下决心的
ex 出 + termin 界限 + ate 使… → 使出界限 → 消灭
in 无 + termin 界限 + able …的 → 没有界限的 → 无穷无尽的
termin 界限 + al …的 → 终结的
termin 界限 + ate 做，造成，使… → 到界限 → 结束
termin 界限 + ation 行为，过程，状态，结果 → 终结
termin 界限 + ology …学 → 限定〔概念〕的学科 → 术语学
termin 界限 + us 表名词，用于科学术语 → 界限的点 → 终点
